SIMPLE: married
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Married
<hw>Mar"ried</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Being in
the state of matrimony; having a spouse; wedded; <as>as, a
<ex>married</ex> man or woman</as>; -- of one person.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to marriage; connubial; <as>as, the
<ex>married</ex> state; one's <ex>married</ex> name</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Wedded to each other; <as>as, a <ex>married</ex>
couple; John and Joan are no longer <ex>married</ex></as>; -- of two
people.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <mark>[fig.]</mark> <def>Joined
to form one object; united.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Marrier</ent>⟦br⟧
